      <hedline>
        <hl1>Estate of the Nation</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eli A Friedman letter holds Nelson W Aldrich Jr's September 3 article would be more convincing if he denied his own use of tax loopholes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>After extracting the essence of an upper-crust upbringing (Harvard, sailboats), Aldrich cheers the estate tax as a pillar of equal opportunity. Clouding his personal finances in obscurity, however (''I am very far from poor''), he would be more convincing if he denied his own use of tax loopholes like real estate and family corporate trusts.</p>
        <p>Eli A. Friedman  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
